#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.13:0.2"
msgid "2. Rājakārāmavagga"
msgstr "2. A Thousand Nuns"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13. Ānandattherasutta → ānandasuttaṃ (bj) | ānanda (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Ānandattherasutta"
msgstr "13. With the Senior Monk Ānanda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.13:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ca ānando āyasmā ca sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharanti "
"jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the venerables Ānanda and Sāriputta were staying near Sāvatthī "
"in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn55.13:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to "
"Venerable Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn55.13:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn55.13:1.4"
msgid ""
"“katinaṃ kho, āvuso ānanda, dhammānaṃ pahānā, katinaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samannāgamanahetu, evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā "
"niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, how many things do people have to give up and how many do they "
"have to possess in order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-"
"enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening?”"

msgctxt "sn55.13:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Catunnaṃ kho, āvuso, dhammānaṃ pahānā, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samannāgamanahetu, evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā "
"niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇāti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, people have to give up four things and possess four things in "
"order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to "
"be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.363"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.13:2.1"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn55.13:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena kho, āvuso, buddhe appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa buddhe appasādo na hoti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t have the distrust in the Buddha that causes an uneducated "
"ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn55.13:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā "
"ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa buddhe aveccappasādo hoti—"
msgstr ""
"And they do have the experiential confidence in the Buddha that causes an "
"educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—"
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn55.13:2.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.13:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dhamme appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa dhamme appasādo na hoti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t have the distrust in the teaching that causes an uneducated "
"ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn55.13:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā "
"ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa dhamme aveccappasādo hoti—"
msgstr ""
"And they do have the experiential confidence in the teaching that causes an "
"educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—"
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn55.13:3.3"
msgid "svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo … pe … viññūhīti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—realizable in this very life, "
"immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible "
"people can know it for themselves.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.13:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, saṅghe appasādena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa saṅghe appasādo na hoti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t have the distrust in the Saṅgha that causes an uneducated "
"ordinary person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn55.13:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato sutavā "
"ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa saṅghe aveccappasādo hoti—"
msgstr ""
"And they do have the experiential confidence in the Saṅgha that causes an "
"educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—"
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn55.13:4.3"
msgid ""
"suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassāti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, "
"straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the "
"eight individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of "
"offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’"
"s offering, and worthy of veneration with joined palms.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.364"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.13:5.1"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpena ca kho, āvuso, dussīlyena samannāgato assutavā puthujjano "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpassa dussīlyaṃ na hoti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t have the unethical conduct that causes an uneducated ordinary "
"person to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—in a place of "
"loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn55.13:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yathārūpehi ca kho, āvuso, ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato sutavā "
"ariyasāvako kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati "
"tathārūpāni ariyakantāni sīlāni honti akhaṇḍāni … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they do have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones that causes an "
"educated noble disciple to be reborn—when their body breaks up, after death—"
"in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn55.13:5.3"
msgid "samādhisaṃvattanikāni."
msgstr ""
"Their ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, unflawed, "
"unblemished, untainted, liberating, praised by sensible people, not "
"mistaken, and leading to immersion."

msgctxt "sn55.13:5.4"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, āvuso, catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānā imesaṃ catunnaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"samannāgamanahetu evamayaṃ pajā bhagavatā byākatā sotāpannā avinipātadhammā "
"niyatā sambodhiparāyaṇā”ti."
msgstr ""
"People have to give up these four things and possess these four things in "
"order for the Buddha to declare that they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to "
"be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.13:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
